  "question_id": "0b1b8219-643f-4811-9df3-d1b449a465b9",
  "short_text": "Numbers in Pyramid",
  "content": "Given two numbers `S` and `N`, write a program to print a **Pyramid** of `N` rows using numbers starting from `S`.\r\n\r\n```\r\n   6\r\n  6 7\r\n 6 7 8\r\n6 7 8 9\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Input\r\n\r\nThe first line of input contains an integer representing `S`.\r\nThe second line of input contains an integer representing `N`.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Output\r\n\r\nThe output should be `N` rows containing numbers starting from `S` as a **Pyramid** shown in the sample output.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Explanation\r\n\r\nFor example, if the given numbers are `S = 7` and `N = 5`,\r\n\r\n- Print the numbers starting from **7** on **5** rows as shown in the given image.\r\n\r\n<Img imageSrc= \"https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-numbers-in-pyramid.png\" widthPercent='70'/>\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\nIn the given image,\r\n\r\n- The Empty box indicates a space (\" \").\r\n- The Number in the box indicates a number (\"7 \").\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\nThe output should be,\r\n\r\n```\r\n    7\r\n   7 8\r\n  7 8 9\r\n 7 8 9 10\r\n7 8 9 10 11\r\n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "ed0a435a-f5bc-4aeb-b0b5-50d96d0b7c46",
      "code_content": "s = int(input())\nn = int(input())\n\nfor row in range(1, n + 1):\n    left_spaces = \" \" * (n - row)\n    each_row = \"\"\n    \n    for column in range(s, row + s):\n        each_row = each_row + str(column) + \" \"\n        \n    each_row = left_spaces + each_row   \n    print(each_row)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
